data.title: Formerly The Chicago School of Professional Psychology
data.meta_description: The Chicago School offers graduate and undergraduate degrees in psychology, counseling, and more online and in Chicago, California, Dallas, and Washington, D.C.

Your Future Starts Here

The Chicago School trains professionals for careers that improve the health of individuals, organizations, and communities. Our practical and solutions-oriented approach has made us a leading nonprofit university for more than 40 years.

Professional and Graduate StudiesUndergraduate Studies

The Chicago School trains graduates to become practitioners and experts in their field. Rigorous curricula prepare you for the next step in your career, whether that step is a licensure examination or further education.

In our undergraduate programs, youâ€™ll study in your chosen field to build the foundational skills necessary for critical research and practical applications. Demonstrating theory and identifying trends in the field prepares you to succeed in the professional world. In addition, many programs include the ability to progress toward a related graduate-level program.

the Chicago School Approach

Practical Experience for a Professional Career

the Chicago School Approach

Practical Experience for a Professional Career

Our curriculum prepares graduates with both theory and practical experience. With years of knowledge of the latest standards and practices, our practitioner-scholar faculty guide you through coursework and hands-on opportunities. Graduates of The Chicago School emerge ready to take action on behalf of those in need.

Admissions

Turn Your Passion into a Career

Take the first step toward building your academic future. Our admissions office is here to help you with your goals and support you on your journey. We have the information you need to start planning: stay informed of program details, requirements, financial resources, and more.
